                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-916" type="given" value="JOHN ALLEN"></interp>JOHN ALLEN BUTLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a baker, living in the Hackney-road—the prisoner was in my service for fourteen months. In consequence of circumstances I marked 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. worth of coppers, and put them into the till—about seven o'clock in the morning on the 23rd of October I came down—the till was locked as I had left it—I opened it, and missed 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in half-pence and a silver sixpence—I sent for the policeman—he desired the pri<lb></lb>soner to turn out his pockets, which he did, and there was one silver six-pence and 3 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in copper, all marked.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You marked some shillings that you found all safe? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—the prisoner has four children—I do not wish to press this against him.</p>
